&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;h4&gt;


üé® Advantages of this implementation:
&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Centralized validation&lt;/strong&gt;: Business rules are in one place&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Immutability&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;code&gt;readonly&lt;/code&gt; properties and &lt;code&gt;clone()&lt;/code&gt; method&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Encapsulation&lt;/strong&gt;: Private fields, controlled access through getters/setters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Safe state transitions&lt;/strong&gt;: You can't go from PENDING to COMPLETED directly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Self-documenting&lt;/strong&gt;: The code clearly explains which operations are valid&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


