&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pros of Separation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚úÖ&lt;strong&gt;Standardization&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî JSON Schema is an open standard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚úÖ &lt;strong&gt;Reusability&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî one data schema can be used in different UIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚úÖ &lt;strong&gt;Validation independent of UI&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî can validate on backend with the same schema&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚úÖ &lt;strong&gt;Ecosystem&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî many tools for JSON Schema (generators, validators, documentation)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚úÖ &lt;strong&gt;Separation of concerns&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî logic separate from presentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cons of Separation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚ùå &lt;strong&gt;Synchronization&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî need to maintain two files in sync&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚ùå &lt;strong&gt;Verbosity&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî more code for simple forms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚ùå &lt;strong&gt;Learning curve&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî need to know both formats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h4&gt;


FormEngine: Unified JSON (Data + UI in One JSON)
&lt;/h4&gt;



